(33, '20', '[{\"question_id\":\"40\",\"answer\":\"Expand outreach to underrepresented communities, anonymized screening for select roles, and ERG-driven awareness.\"},{\"question_id\":\"41\",\"answer\":\"Inclusion is tracked through engagement pulse surveys and quarterly review of inclusive behaviors across leadership levels.\"},{\"question_id\":\"42\",\"answer\":\"Use of structured rubrics, bias interrupter prompts during interviews, and training for hiring panels.\"},{\"question_id\":\"43\",\"answer\":\"It\'s a foundational pillar \\u2014 our culture and innovation strategy both rely on a diverse, inclusive workforce.\"}]', '6', '6', '8', '11', 'Our goal this year is to increase brand awareness in North America. Can you help me assess this and guide the team?', 'Of course! Here are some steps to assess and guide the team in increasing brand awareness in North America:\n\n1. Market Research: Conduct market research to identify current awareness levels of your brand in North America. You can use surveys, focus groups, and social media listening tools to gather insights on brand perception and reach.\n\n2. Identify Target Audience: Determine your target audience in North America and understand their demographics, interests, and behaviors. This will help in tailoring your brand awareness efforts to effectively reach and resonate with them.\n\n3. Competitive Analysis: Analyze the brand awareness strategies of your competitors in North America to understand what is working for them and how you can differentiate your own brand messaging and positioning.\n\n4. Develop a Brand Awareness Strategy: Based on the insights gathered from market research and competitor analysis, develop a comprehensive brand awareness strategy for North America. This may include a mi', 0, 0, '2025-04-21 17:44:01'),
(34, '20', '[{\"question_id\":\"40\",\"answer\":\"Expand outreach to underrepresented communities, anonymized screening for select roles, and ERG-driven awareness.\"},{\"question_id\":\"41\",\"answer\":\"Inclusion is tracked through engagement pulse surveys and quarterly review of inclusive behaviors across leadership levels.\"},{\"question_id\":\"42\",\"answer\":\"Use of structured rubrics, bias interrupter prompts during interviews, and training for hiring panels.\"},{\"question_id\":\"43\",\"answer\":\"It\'s a foundational pillar \\u2014 our culture and innovation strategy both rely on a diverse, inclusive workforce.\"}]', '6', '6', '8', '11', 'I want to enhance employee wellness this year — where do I start?', 'There are many ways to enhance employee wellness in the workplace. Here are some ideas to get you started:\n\n1. Develop a wellness program: Create a comprehensive wellness program that includes activities and resources to support physical, mental, and emotional health. This could include fitness challenges, healthy eating initiatives, stress management workshops, and mental health resources.\n\n2. Provide resources for physical health: Offer onsite fitness classes, encourage walking meetings, provide standing desks, and offer healthy snacks in the office.\n\n3. Promote work-life balance: Encourage employees to take breaks, use their vacation time, and leave work at a reasonable hour. Offer flexible work arrangements, such as telecommuting or flexible hours, to help employees balance their work and personal lives.\n\n4. Focus on mental health: Provide access to mental health resources, such as counseling services or mental health awareness training. Encourage open communication about mental he', 0, 0, '2025-04-21 18:33:14'),
(35, '20', '[{\"question_id\":\"40\",\"answer\":\"Expand outreach to underrepresented communities, anonymized screening for select roles, and ERG-driven awareness.\"},{\"question_id\":\"41\",\"answer\":\"Inclusion is tracked through engagement pulse surveys and quarterly review of inclusive behaviors across leadership levels.\"},{\"question_id\":\"42\",\"answer\":\"Use of structured rubrics, bias interrupter prompts during interviews, and training for hiring panels.\"},{\"question_id\":\"43\",\"answer\":\"It\'s a foundational pillar \\u2014 our culture and innovation strategy both rely on a diverse, inclusive workforce.\"}]', '6', '6', '8', '11', 'Is my goal realistic and achieveable based on past history', 'It is difficult to determine whether a goal is realistic and achievable based solely on past history, as past performance may not always be indicative of future results. However, if you have successfully achieved similar goals in the past, or have the necessary skills, resources, and support systems in place to help you reach your goal, it may be more likely to be realistic and achievable. It is also important to set specific, measurable, attainable, relevant, and time-bound (SMART) goals to increase the likelihood of success. Ultimately, the determination of whether a goal is realistic and achievable will depend on your individual circumstances and commitment to reaching that goal.', 0, 0, '2025-04-21 18:34:20'),
