(108, '20', '[{\"question_id\":\"69\",\"answer\":\"test\"},{\"question_id\":\"70\",\"answer\":\"test\"},{\"question_id\":\"71\",\"answer\":\"test\"},{\"question_id\":\"72\",\"answer\":\"test\"}]', '3', '9', '14', '21', 'I want to enhance employee wellness this year — where do I start?', '✅ Final Outcome Summary  \n\nRecommendation: Start by conducting a thorough assessment of your current employee wellness programs and resources to identify areas for improvement and expansion. Consider incorporating both physical and mental wellness initiatives to create a holistic approach. Set a timeline of 1 month to complete the assessment. Next step options include either launching a pilot program for a specific wellness initiative or creating a comprehensive strategy for overall employee wellness.\n\n🧩 Step 1: Chat Acknowledgement  \n- Acknowledge the user’s goal in a strategic, co-pilot tone. Ask if document scan is needed.  \n\n📁 Step 2: Document Insights  \n- The user has expressed a desire to enhance employee wellness this year. No specific documents have been provided.\n\n📊 Step 3: Goal Assessment Summary  \n- Complexity: Moderate  \n- Resource Requirements: Medium  \n- Strategic Alignment: High  \n- Assign Aggressiveness: Moderate  \n\n📈 Step 4: Scoring  \n- Impact: 8/10  \n- Feasibility: 6/10  \n- Alignment: 9/10  \n- Total Score: 23/30  \n- Strengths: Strong alignment with current organizational goals.  \n- Risks: Potential lack of employee engagement if not communicated effectively.  \n\n🗺️ Step 5: Strategy Map  \n- Path 1: Conduct an employee survey to gather feedback and insights. Estimated Effort: 2 weeks, Risk: Low, ROI Potential: High.  \n- Path 2: Implement a wellness challenge program. Estimated Effort: 1 month, Risk: Moderate, ROI Potential: Moderate.  \n- Path 3: Partner with a wellness vendor for comprehensive services. Estimated Effort: 3 months, Risk: High, ROI Potential: High.  \nRecommendation: Path 1 - Conduct an employee survey to gather insights and feedback to inform your wellness strategy.\n\n🔮 Step 6: Scenario Simulations  \n- Option A: Employee Survey - Timeline: 2 weeks, Metrics: Participation rate, feedback quality, Risk Level: Low.  \n- Option B: Wellness Challenge Program - Timeline: 1 month, Metrics: Employee engagement, behavior change, Risk Level: Moderate.  \nRecommendation: Option A - Employee Survey is the best-fit scenario for gaining valuable insights from employees.\n\n👥 Step 7: Rephrased Goals by Role  \n- HR Manager: Enhance engagement through wellness initiatives.  \n- Team Leads: Incorporate wellness activities into team bonding events.  \n- Finance Manager: Evaluate cost-effective wellness solutions for implementation.  \nComplementary Goals:  \n- Synergistic sub-goals could include tying wellness program participation to performance reviews. Synergy Level: Strong.', 0, 0, '2025-05-22 18:30:59'),
(109, '20', '[{\"question_id\":\"69\",\"answer\":\"test\"},{\"question_id\":\"70\",\"answer\":\"test\"},{\"question_id\":\"71\",\"answer\":\"test\"},{\"question_id\":\"72\",\"answer\":\"test\"}]', '3', '9', '14', '21', 'Our goal this year is to increase brand awareness in North America. Can you help me assess this and guide the team?', '🧩 Step 1: Chat Acknowledgement  \n- Acknowledge the user\'s goal to increase brand awareness in North America.  \n- Ask if a document scan is needed.  \n\n📁 Step 2: Document Insights  \n- No specific documents are needed for this goal assessment.  \n\n📊 Step 3: Goal Assessment Summary  \n- Complexity: Moderate  \n- Resource Requirements: Moderate  \n- Strategic Alignment: High  \n- Assign Aggressiveness: Aggressive  \n\n📈 Step 4: Scoring  \n- Impact: 8/10  \n- Feasibility: 7/10  \n- Alignment: 9/10  \n- Total Score: 24/30  \n- Interpretation: Overall, this goal shows promising potential but may require significant effort.\n\n🗺️ Step 5: Strategy Map  \n- Path 1: Partnership with Influencers  \n- Path 2: Social Media Campaign  \n- Path 3: Sponsored Events in Key Cities  \n- Recommend: Social Media Campaign  \n\n🔮 Step 6: Scenario Simulations  \n- Option A: Launch Social Media Campaign in Q3  \n- Option B: Partner with Influencers for the full year  \n- Recommend: Option A for quicker impact.\n\n👥 Step 7: Rephrased Goals by Role  \n- Marketing Manager: Increase organic reach by 20% by year-end.  \n- Sales Director: Generate 15% more leads from North America.  \n- Digital Marketing Specialist: Improve brand engagement on social media by 25%.  \n- Content Creator: Create compelling brand stories for North American audience.  \n- Customer Success Manager: Highlight success stories from North American clients.  \n📌 Complementary Goals  \n- Implement social listening to track brand sentiment.  \n- Synergy Level: Strong.', 0, 0, '2025-05-22 18:33:18'),
