(12, '35', '20', '[{\"question_id\":\"40\",\"answer\":\"Expand outreach to underrepresented communities, anonymized screening for select roles, and ERG-driven awareness.\"},{\"question_id\":\"41\",\"answer\":\"Inclusion is tracked through engagement pulse surveys and quarterly review of inclusive behaviors across leadership levels.\"},{\"question_id\":\"42\",\"answer\":\"Use of structured rubrics, bias interrupter prompts during interviews, and training for hiring panels.\"},{\"question_id\":\"43\",\"answer\":\"It\'s a foundational pillar \\u2014 our culture and innovation strategy both rely on a diverse, inclusive workforce.\"}]', '6', '6', '8', '11', 'Is my goal realistic and achieveable based on past history', 'It is difficult to determine whether a goal is realistic and achievable based solely on past history, as past performance may not always be indicative of future results. However, if you have successfully achieved similar goals in the past, or have the necessary skills, resources, and support systems in place to help you reach your goal, it may be more likely to be realistic and achievable. It is also important to set specific, measurable, attainable, relevant, and time-bound (SMART) goals to increase the likelihood of success. Ultimately, the determination of whether a goal is realistic and achievable will depend on your individual circumstances and commitment to reaching that goal.', '2025-04-21 18:57:27'),
