(Recommended Path)*  \n   - **Description:** Align department goals under a unified organizational objective.  \n   - **Estimated Effort:** Medium  \n   - **Risk:** Low  \n   - **ROI Potential:** High  \n\n🔮 **Step 6: Scenario Simulations**  \n- **Option A:** Implement Unified Communication Platform  \n  - **Timeline:** Q1–Q2 2024  \n  - **Metrics:** Adoption rate, collaboration metrics  \n  - **Risk Level:** Low  \n- **Option B:** Introduce Shared Goal Framework  \n  - **Timeline:** Q1–Q2 2024  \n  - **Metrics:** Goal alignment score, project completion rates  \n  - **Risk Level:** Low  \n\n**Recommended Scenario:** Option B – Shared Goal Framework for its high ROI potential and strategic alignment.\n\n👥 **Step 7: Rephrased Goals by Role**  \n1. **Chief Technology Officer (CTO):**  \n   - **Relevance Score:** High  \n   - **Goal:** Integrate technology to enhance communication channels.  \n2. **Human Resources (HR) Manager:**  \n   - **Relevance Score:** Medium  \n   - **Goal:** Facilitate workshops to train employees on collaboration tools.  \n3. **Department Heads:**  \n   - **Relevance Score:** High  \n   - **Goal:** Align departmental KPIs with overarching collaboration objectives.\n\n📌 **Complementary Goals**  \n1. Develop a rewards program for successful cross-department projects.  \n   - **Synergy Level:** Strong  \n2. Increase transparency in project timelines and objectives across all departments.  \n   - **Synergy Level:** Needs Validation\n\nBy addressing these comprehensive steps, the organization can effectively improve cross-departmental collaboration, fostering a more unified and efficient work environment.', '2025-05-29 05:25:44'),
