(34, '40', '[{\"question_id\":\"94\",\"answer\":\"Two Directors in Engineering and one in Product Ops were hired during our scaling phase\"},{\"question_id\":\"95\",\"answer\":\"Approximately 50%. \\r\\nEngineering and Customer Ops have surfaced issues in pulse surveys and exit interviews related to misaligned expectations from new leadership.\"},{\"question_id\":\"96\",\"answer\":\"18% overall.\\r\\nWith a peak of 28% in Customer Ops and 22% in Engineering.\"},{\"question_id\":\"97\",\"answer\":\"Somewhat.\\r\\nParticipation is inconsistent. Sales and Product contribute actively, but Engineering and Ops tend to receive goals post-finalization\"},{\"question_id\":\"98\",\"answer\":\"Lack of shared visibility and sync rhythm.\\r\\nThere\\u2019s no centralized tool for surfacing interdependencies or goal readiness across departments. It results in delays and duplicated efforts.\"}]', '6', '12', '23', '32', 0, 1, 1, '2025-07-04 18:32:52', '2025-07-04 19:18:39'),
(35, '41', '[{\"question_id\":\"99\",\"answer\":\"Curiosity\\r\\n\\r\\nCraftsmanship\\r\\n\\r\\nCustomer Obsession\\r\\n\\r\\nOwnership\\r\\n(These values guided us when we were a 5-person startup \\u2014 we still hire and promote based on them.)\"},{\"question_id\":\"100\",\"answer\":\"Yes \\u2014 we have a culture deck and onboarding playbook that captures our origin story, core beliefs, and how we made decisions early on. But only a few teams refer to it actively now.\"},{\"question_id\":\"101\",\"answer\":\"Ownership. I want everyone \\u2014 regardless of level \\u2014 to take initiative like they\\u2019re running the company.\"},{\"question_id\":\"102\",\"answer\":\"We\\u2019re hiring 8\\u201310 people per month across Tech, Customer Ops, and Sales. That\\u2019s over 35% growth expected this year.\"},{\"question_id\":\"103\",\"answer\":\"Not officially. Our People & Culture team tries to hold the line, but we don\\u2019t have embedded culture leads within each department.\"}]', '5', '17', '24', '33', 0, 1, 1, '2025-07-08 17:01:08', '2025-11-12 23:31:46'),
(36, '43', '[{\"question_id\":\"109\",\"answer\":\"We use informal input from functional heads and spreadsheets to track readiness. There\'s no consistent framework across initiatives.\"},{\"question_id\":\"110\",\"answer\":\"Yes. We lost a key B2B partner last quarter because our support team wasn\\u2019t fully prepared during onboarding \\u2014 it reflected poorly on us.\"},{\"question_id\":\"111\",\"answer\":\"People readiness and process clarity are the biggest culprits. Sometimes Sales pushes forward while Ops or Product is still catching up.\"},{\"question_id\":\"112\",\"answer\":\"It\\u2019s usually ad hoc \\u2014 I or a project lead takes initiative, but we don\\u2019t have a dedicated role or system for this.\"},{\"question_id\":\"113\",\"answer\":\"We estimate it manually during planning. But we rarely track actual ramp-up vs projected \\u2014 and that\\u2019s a gap I\\u2019d like to fix.\"}]', '11', '18', '26', '35', 0, 1, 0, '2025-07-08 19:05:19', '2025-07-08 19:16:59'),
(37, '44', '[{\"question_id\":\"104\",\"answer\":\"I currently manage ~60 engineers split across backend, frontend, and DevOps squads. Each team is led by a tech lead reporting to me.\"},{\"question_id\":\"105\",\"answer\":\"Not really. I get quarterly engagement scores and the occasional exit interview summary, but I lack visibility into real-time risk or sentiment.\"},{\"question_id\":\"106\",\"answer\":\"Retention-related decisions. For example, deciding whether to promote someone, move them to another squad, or coach them \\u2014 it\'s mostly gut-driven right now.\"},{\"question_id\":\"107\",\"answer\":\"I\\u2019m expected to \\u201ckeep people engaged\\u201d and maintain performance, but there\\u2019s no formal metric or framework tied to culture health or turnover mitigation.\"},{\"question_id\":\"108\",\"answer\":\"We monitor sprint velocity, incident recovery time, PR turnaround, and bug resolution \\u2014 but none of that tells me if people are burnt out or thinking of leaving.\"}]', '9', '13', '25', '34', 0, 1, 0, '2025-07-08 19:27:54', '2025-07-08 19:45:43'),
(38, '45', '[{\"question_id\":\"57\",\"answer\":\"Our strategic objectives are to increase global market share, leverage international talent, diversify revenue streams, and position ElevateX Solutions as a globally recognized leader in SaaS-based project management solutions.\"},{\"question_id\":\"58\",\"answer\":\"We\\u2019re targeting Europe (specifically the UK and Germany) and Asia-Pacific (Singapore and Australia), given their mature technology infrastructure, demand for digital transformation solutions, and strong market potential for SaaS adoption.\"},{\"question_id\":\"59\",\"answer\":\"We anticipate challenges such as cultural differences, regulatory compliance, local competition, establishing brand trust, and managing logistical complexities in international operations.\"},{\"question_id\":\"60\",\"answer\":\"We plan to manage global complexities through strategic local partnerships, implementing robust governance structures, leveraging cloud-based collaboration tools, and maintaining cultural alignment through targeted training and continuous communication.\"}]', '5', '7', '11', '18', 0, 1, 1, '2025-07-22 14:33:23', '2025-08-03 11:12:02'),
(39, '41', '[{\"question_id\":\"53\",\"answer\":\"adfadf\"},{\"question_id\":\"54\",\"answer\":\"adfadf\"},{\"question_id\":\"55\",\"answer\":\"adfasdf\"},{\"question_id\":\"56\",\"answer\":\"asdfsdaf\"}]', '5', '7', '10', '17', 0, 1, 0, '2025-11-12 23:48:48', '2025-11-12 23:49:45');

